---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
// Import organizing photos
import organizing24 from '../../assets/organizing/24.jpg';
import organizing27 from '../../assets/organizing/27.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout>
	<Fragment slot="head">
		<BaseHead title={`Strike Ready Philadelphia | Solidarity & Mutual Aid - ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Strike Ready provides strategic support and mutual aid for workers' actions in Philadelphia. Building solidarity, people power, and working class power through rapid-response support for strikes, protests, and community actions." keywords="strike support Philadelphia, solidarity, mutual aid, people power, working class power, worker justice, labor-community coalition, strike fund Philadelphia" />
		<style>
		main {
			width: 100%;
			max-width: 1000px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 0;
			box-sizing: border-box;
			overflow-x: hidden;
		}
		.intro-section {
			background: var(--white);
			padding: 0 2em 2.5em;
		}
		.intro-section p {
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			line-height: 1.8;
			font-size: 1.05em;
			margin-bottom: 1.5em;
			max-width: 850px;
			margin-left: auto;
			margin-right: auto;
		}
		.intro-section p:last-child {
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}
		.vision-callout {
			background: var(--canary-yellow);
			padding: 1.5em 2em;
			border-radius: 8px;
			margin: 2em auto;
			max-width: 850px;
			border-left: 5px solid var(--deep-space-blue);
			text-align: center;
		}
		.vision-callout p {
			margin: 0 !important;
			font-weight: 600;
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
		}
		.image-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
			gap: 1.5em;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 2em;
			max-width: 950px;
			background: var(--white);
		}
		.image-grid img {
			width: 100%;
			height: 280px;
			object-fit: cover;
			border-radius: 8px;
			box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(1, 47, 64, 0.2);
		}
		.committees-section {
			background: rgba(190, 202, 207, 0.2);
			padding: 3em 2em;
		}
		.committees-section h2 {
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			text-align: center;
			font-size: 2em;
			margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;
		}
		.committees-section > p {
			text-align: center;
			max-width: 750px;
			margin: 0 auto 2em;
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			line-height: 1.7;
		}
		.committees-section h3 {
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			text-align: center;
			margin: 2em 0 1.5em;
			font-size: 1.4em;
		}
		.role-cards {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
			gap: 1.5em;
			max-width: 950px;
			margin: 0 auto;
		}
		.role-card {
			background: var(--white);
			padding: 1.5em;
			border-radius: 8px;
			box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(1, 47, 64, 0.1);
			border-top: 4px solid var(--sky-surge);
			transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
		}
		.role-card:hover {
			transform: translateY(-3px);
			box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(1, 47, 64, 0.15);
		}
		.role-card strong {
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			display: block;
			font-size: 1.1em;
			margin-bottom: 0.5em;
		}
		.role-card p {
			color: #555;
			line-height: 1.6;
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.95em;
		}
		.join-section {
			background: var(--deep-space-blue);
			color: var(--white);
			padding: 3em 2em;
			text-align: center;
		}
		.join-section h2 {
			color: var(--white);
			margin: 0 0 1em 0;
			font-size: 2em;
		}
		.join-section .btn {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: 1em 2.5em;
			background: var(--canary-yellow);
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			text-decoration: none;
			border-radius: 6px;
			font-weight: 700;
			font-size: 1.1em;
			transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
		}
		.join-section .btn:hover {
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
		}
		.fund-section {
			background: var(--white);
			padding: 3em 2em;
		}
		.fund-section h2 {
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			text-align: center;
			font-size: 2em;
			margin: 0 0 1em 0;
		}
		.fund-section > p {
			max-width: 800px;
			margin: 0 auto 2em;
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			line-height: 1.7;
			text-align: center;
		}
		.fund-list {
			max-width: 800px;
			margin: 0 auto 2em;
			padding-left: 2em;
		}
		.fund-list li {
			color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			line-height: 1.8;
			margin-bottom: 0.75em;
		}
		.donate-cta {
			text-align: center;
			margin-top: 2em;
		}
		.donate-cta .btn {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: 1.25em 3em;
			background: var(--deep-space-blue);
			color: var(--white);
			text-decoration: none;
			border-radius: 6px;
			font-weight: 700;
			font-size: 1.4em;
			transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s, background 0.2s;
		}
		.donate-cta .btn:hover {
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(1, 47, 64, 0.3);
			background: var(--sky-surge);
		}
		@media (max-width: 768px) {
			.intro-section,
			.committees-section,
			.join-section,
			.fund-section {
				padding: 2em 1.5em;
			}
			.committees-section h2,
			.fund-section h2 {
				font-size: 1.6em;
			}
			.role-cards {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}
		}
		</style>
	</Fragment>
	<main>
			<Hero title="Strike Ready: Revolution Ready" subtitle="Building infrastructure for solidarity, mutual aid, and collective action" />

			<div class="image-grid">
				<Image src={organizing24} alt="Strategic support and organizing" />
				<Image src={organizing27} alt="Community action and solidarity" />
			</div>

			<section class="intro-section">
				<p>When workers go on strike or communities rise in protest and rallies, there is no ready framework for rapid strategic support—no infrastructure for mobilizing communications, legal aid, safety planning, or public messaging. This leaves actions under-resourced and vulnerable to burnout or repression. From permits and sound systems to legal observers and medics, organizing a protest, a rally or strike often relies on ad-hoc efforts and individual resource-pooling. Without a central hub for materials and logistical support, each action is reinventing the wheel, limiting impact and sustainability.</p>

				<p>Poor and working-class communities—those most likely to organize—often lack access to the most basic resources during people's actions. There are few mechanisms in place to provide food, water, transportation, and shelter to sustain people during prolonged protests, strikes, or occupations.</p>

				<div class="vision-callout">
					<p>We envision a bold new framework that bridges unions and community groups, ensures strategic readiness, and provides real-time mutual aid and infrastructure during moments of action.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="committees-section">
				<h2>Strike Ready Committees</h2>
				<p>Strike Ready Committees are local teams organized by Jobs with Justice to prepare communities and workers to stand in powerful solidarity with each other. They build the skills, infrastructure, and leadership needed to fight against billionaires and corporations.</p>

				<h3>Role of Strike Ready Committees</h3>
				<div class="role-cards">
					<div class="role-card">
						<strong>Support Peoples' Actions</strong>
						<p>Provide community solidarity for protests, strikes, walkouts, and direct actions</p>
					</div>
					<div class="role-card">
						<strong>Train & Develop Leaders</strong>
						<p>Equip members with skills in de-escalation, legal rights, strike support, fundraising, action planning, and power analysis</p>
					</div>
					<div class="role-card">
						<strong>Build Rapid Response Infrastructure</strong>
						<p>Maintain systems for protests, rallies, and picket-line support, strike/bail funds, rides, and safety coordination</p>
					</div>
					<div class="role-card">
						<strong>Mobilize Working Class Power</strong>
						<p>Coordinate local solidarity actions, build structures, amplify worker struggles through media and social platforms, and build durable public support networks</p>
					</div>
					<div class="role-card">
						<strong>Grow Long-Term Capacity</strong>
						<p>Serve as an ongoing on-ramp and training ground for new activists and existing leaders</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="join-section">
				<h2>Join Strike Ready Committees</h2>
				<p style="color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 1.5em; line-height: 1.6;">If you have any questions, please reach out to us, either by email (<a href="mailto:muzammal@phillyjwj.org" style="color: var(--canary-yellow); text-decoration: underline;">muzammal@phillyjwj.org</a>) or <a href="https://calendly.com/muzammal-phillyjwj/30min" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--canary-yellow); text-decoration: underline;">by scheduling a meeting</a>!</p>
				<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1OQLVSofjHVyG5FDtF6tlruzIfZhlXUChEvo-f8Z0qt8/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn">Sign Up Now</a>
			</section>

			<section class="fund-section">
				<h2>People's Action Fund</h2>
				<p>People's action fund provides sustainable, independent funding that allows communities to organize and advocate for change without relying on corporate or political interests. By being rooted in grassroots fundraising, union solidarity, and philanthropy, it ensures that power and resources stay with the people most affected by the issues they are fighting to address.</p>
				
				<ul class="fund-list">
					<li>Support and fund people's actions i.e. rallies, protests, strikes etc. in Philadelphia</li>
					<li>Distribute food/water support during direct actions</li>
					<li>Offer micro-grants for community groups or strike committees</li>
					<li>Maintain a supply hub for protest materials, safety gear, and medical kits</li>
					<li>Finance transportation and accommodation for displaced or vulnerable organizers</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="donate-cta">
					<a href="/donate" class="btn">Donate</a>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
</BaseLayout>

